d 'XTKUMBLIENHARD': module to Estimate Generalized Four-Component Panel Data Stochastic Frontier Models
d
d  xtkumblienhard is a powerful and user-friendly Stata command
d designed to estimate Generalized Four-Component Panel Data
d Stochastic Frontier Models, all in a single line of code. This
d package streamlines the estimation of a sophisticated stochastic
d frontier framework where the composite error term is decomposed
d into four distinct components: unobserved individual
d heterogeneity, persistent inefficiency, transitory inefficiency
d and random noise. By clearly separating these sources of
d variation, xtkumblienhard enables researchers to gain deeper
d insights into performance dynamics across panel data settings.
d This model builds on the influential and excellent works of
d Kumbhakar, Lien and Hardaker (Journal of Productivity Analysis,
d 2014), Kumbhakar, Wang and Horncastle (Cambridge University
d Press, 2015), and Nguyen, Sickles and Zelenyuk (Springer, 2022),
d who originally implemented it through multi-step procedures. The
d innovation of xtkumblienhard lies in its simplicity: it brings
d the full power of this four-component framework to Stata users
d with native ADO language syntax, eliminating the need for complex
d coding or external scripts. Rather than replacing these
d foundational and outstanding contributions, xtkumblienhard
d democratizes access to advanced stochastic frontier analysis,
d making it faster, easier, and more intuitive for applied
d researchers, analysts, and students alike. Whether you are
d studying firm-level productivity, benchmarking efficiency, or
d exploring heterogeneity in performance, xtkumblienhard is your
d go-to tool for robust and elegant estimation. 
d
d KW: panel data
d KW: stochastic frontier model
d
d Requires: Stata version 18
d
d Distribution-Date: 20260107
d
d Author: Diallo Ibrahima Amadou
d Support: email zavren@@gmail.com
d
f xtkumblienhard.ado
f xtkumblienhard.sthlp
